    <section id="about">
        <h2>About Us</h2>
        <p>At student organisation, we are on a mission to combat the global challenge of food waste and champion sustainable living. Founded with a passion for environmental conservation and a commitment to fostering positive change, our organization is dedicated to reshaping the way we approach and manage food resources.

Our journey began with a simple yet powerful belief: every morsel matters. With one-third of the world's food going to waste annually, we felt compelled to act. Our team comprises enthusiastic individuals from diverse backgrounds, each bringing unique expertise to the table. From environmental scientists to passionate advocates, we collaborate to develop and promote practical solutions for reducing food waste at every level of society.

Through extensive research, community engagement, and strategic partnerships, we aim to raise awareness about the environmental, social, and economic implications of food waste. By providing educational resources, organizing events, and collaborating with businesses, we empower individuals and communities to adopt sustainable practices that minimize their impact on the planet.</p>
      </section>

    <section id="blog">
        <h2>Blog</h2>
		<h4>Title: "Tackling Food Waste: A Recipe for Sustainability"</h4>
        <p>In a world where millions go hungry, the staggering amount of food waste demands urgent attention. Our responsibility to manage food waste is paramount for a sustainable future. By adopting mindful consumption habits, such as meal planning and proper storage, individuals can significantly reduce their contribution to this global predicament. Embracing a 'zero-waste' lifestyle doesn't require drastic changes; it starts with conscious choices.

Restaurants and grocery stores also play pivotal roles in food waste management. Partnerships with local organizations can redirect surplus food to those in need, fostering a sense of community responsibility. Composting is another impactful solution, converting organic waste into nutrient-rich soil. As we navigate these solutions, we contribute not only to waste reduction but also to a healthier planet. Each meal saved is a step towards a more sustainable and compassionate world. Together, let's savor the flavor of responsible living while nourishing our communities and the environment.</p>
    <img src="C:\Users\DELL\OneDrive\Desktop\786003fdec2ec0cf182066abe3e1b998.jpg" alt="About Food Waste Management">
